    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-06-08T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-06-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-08T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 8, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Supplementing Department’s 7, June 7, 6 p.m. Your attention is called to
                    Sections 424, 425 and 431 of Title 18 of the Criminal Code of United States and
                    particularly to the employment therein of the expression “to be held to service
                    or labor”. In the event that the shipment in question is made the Department
                    expects to confer with <pb facs="0395" n="277" xml:id="pg_277"/> the Attorney
                    General of the United States with a view to considering the possibility of
                    initiating criminal proceedings under these sections.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
